Sasalin spewed a jet of flame, the tall Slakian igniting a small patch of forest before circling overhead, watching for the right moment. Strangely, when he slowed down, the eerie shrieks behind him also stopped. Sasalin forgot that there was a passenger on his back.
"Come on, Tenruk, you've transformed into a Slakian before!"
"Flying on your own is one thing, but being suddenly dragged away by a huge pink dragon is entirely different!"
"Are you okay, Kayer?"
Kayer clearly disagreed with Nisi's words; he looked paler than usual, and his claws had dug deep into Sasalin's back, drawing blood from the Slakian, but Sasalin obviously didn't care. That said, Sasalin realized he had scared his new friend and decided to land in an open area.
"Sorry, sorry, I smelled something. I need to deal with it!"
"Do you have to drag us along too?" Tenruk climbed down from Sasalin's back, sliding down the tail to the ground, and asked sharply. "We left Retvik behind! We abandoned that strong, combative big guy! How will he ever find us?"
"He'll figure it out..." Nisi nodded. "Retvik is slow, but he's not stupid."
"Will Retvik know how to drive?"
Nisi blinked, then looked at Tenruk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like Kayer's. He started taking the car to work purely because you always drove us to work. He only has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasalin suddenly burst into laughter, but no one knew why. It took Sasalin a while before he calmed down.
"Sorry, sorry, I just imagined your big, armored friend riding a little bicycle designed for Temson children. That picture is too ridiculous! I wish I had telepathy. That idea is too interesting! I definitely need to treasure it!"
Kayer also laughed, because he could imagine what Sasalin was thinking. "Okay, okay. But what did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?"
Sasalin hummed, took off quickly, and then disappeared, only to fly back and drop a corpse in front of Nisi. It was an Orosarack, a very rare golden-white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "Another one has died. I heard their cries. I smelled their blood. I must protect them, hunt down the killer. This is Isini's will. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slakian suddenly froze. Nisi and Kayer also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the clearing. A huge, pitch-black thing was staring at them, hissing. The thing suddenly spread its two pairs of giant wings and charged forward, directly aiming at Sasalin, completely ignoring the three small figures standing in its way. Kayer and Tenuk barely managed to get out of the way, but Nisi found herself being thrown to the ground, almost landing on Sasalin.
Sasalin grabbed Nisi, using his long and agile tail to throw her onto his back, then took to the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly gave chase.
Kayer muttered, pulled a rifle from behind his back, and opened his bag to take out a belt of bullets. He hung the bullet belt around his chest for easy access, but quickly realized that Nisi, Sasalin, and the monster were gone.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Kayer asked.
"You want to go after them?"
"Nonsense."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? This rifle in my hand is powerful, and I can fire at any time. I just need to see it, and I can bring it down."
Tenruk hesitated for a moment, then took a step back to give himself some space. With a low, slightly painful groan, Tenruk's body stretched out, his fur turned into scales, and his arms turned into wings. He soon transformed into an ordinary light blue Slak, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Tenuk now looked like a more ordinary Slakian, with neatly arranged scales on his back and a pair of spikes, making it easier for Kayer to grab him. It took Tenuk a long time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly adjusted his direction and struggled to catch up.
However, Tenuk and Kayer soon realized they were not facing just one opponent. A second dark monster emerged from below them, and Tenuk barely avoided the collision.
"I guess this is the other terrible big monster that Larnex was worried about?" Kayer frowned, trying to shoot at the second monster but missing, he quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not respond; he was busy flying toward Nisi and Sasalin, despite the other monster chasing them. Kayer awkwardly turned around to face the monster. The monster was chasing them, and Kayer considered this a good thing because it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, causing it to roar in pain and disappear into the forest. Kayer was unsure if it was still following them, but he felt it certainly couldn't keep up.
Ahead, Sasalin was wildly thrashing his body, spraying fire at the black monster, while Nisi desperately held onto Sasalin to prevent herself from falling. Although the monster was certainly injured, it seemed enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs seemed to have caused little damage. After stabilizing his body, Sasalin allowed Nisi to take the opportunity to pull out her weapon, a shotgun she trusted. Of course, the shotgun could not deal with such a monster, but the scattered bullets might at least scare off this black beast?
